Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.74,0:00:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.33,0:00:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.64,0:00:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, the next version of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.98,0:00:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your app will have no graphical
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.06,0:00:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,UI at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.69,0:00:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you interact with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.94,0:00:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What could that sound like?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.81,0:00:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Hugo Verweij, sound designer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.44,0:00:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Human Interface team.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the pleasure on working of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.66,0:00:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,many of the sounds you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.30,0:00:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,through your Apple devices, and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.62,0:00:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I love thinking about these kind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.35,0:00:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.13,0:00:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There are probably some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.83,0:00:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,musicians in the room, maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.23,0:01:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,even one or two sound designers,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.60,0:01:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is by no means required
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.30,0:01:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for this talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.80,0:01:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This session is for everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.59,0:01:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you've never recorded a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.91,0:01:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,single sound in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.44,0:01:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also not going to teach you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.36,0:01:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how to become a sound designer,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.78,0:01:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but I hope I'm going to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.26,0:01:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,some ideas of how to incorporate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.66,0:01:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,sound in your design process and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.23,0:01:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,why it makes sense to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.85,0:01:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as a developer, you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.47,0:01:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,lot on your plate and adding
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.91,0:01:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,sound to your app is probably
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.49,0:01:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,not super high on your to-do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.45,0:01:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,list, but I like to make the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.93,0:01:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,case that sound, if used the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.54,0:01:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,right way, really can help
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.33,0:01:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,transform the experience of your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,product.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.19,0:01:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now at Apple and at WWDC, we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.76,0:01:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,talk a lot about visual design.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.85,0:01:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For now though, let's just try
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to use our ears for a little
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.39,0:01:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,while.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.32,0:01:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask you all to just
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,close your eyes for one minute,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.37,0:02:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and imagine you're in a forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.09,0:02:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This might help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.52,0:02:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Forest sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.05,0:02:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quiet afternoon, and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.18,0:02:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.02,0:02:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Footstep sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.02,0:02:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Birds squawking ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.18,0:02:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather seems very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.56,0:02:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But then [phone notification
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.85,0:02:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sound] Dark Sky is predicting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.92,0:02:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.12,0:02:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You better pick up the pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.52,0:02:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Footstep Sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:03:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Rain and Thunder Sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.82,0:03:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you can open your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.77,0:03:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're not in a forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.67,0:03:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're actually at WWDC.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound has this magical ability
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.03,0:03:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to calm us down, to get on our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.76,0:03:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nerves, to scare us, or to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,delight us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.44,0:03:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When we close our eyes, it has
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.11,0:03:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the power to transport us to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.86,0:03:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,places.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.53,0:03:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to talk about the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,following things today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why sound is an important aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.16,0:03:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of design, designing sounds for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.49,0:03:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications, designing sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.94,0:03:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for UI elements, and some tips
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.39,0:03:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and techniques to get you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.10,0:03:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.45,0:03:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound is everywhere, all around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.55,0:03:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,us, and we never really pay much
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.65,0:03:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.52,0:04:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Church Bell Ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Church bells have been telling
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.46,0:04:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the time for many centuries in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.08,0:04:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,countries all across the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.42,0:04:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,like here in my beautiful home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.99,0:04:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,town, Amsterdam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They tell us the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.55,0:04:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They tell us where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.79,0:04:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They give us a sense of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.88,0:04:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We also use our ears for an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.25,0:04:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,early warning system, like when
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we're about to cross the street
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and we hear this --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.25,0:04:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[car accelerating] [brakes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,screeching]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.72,0:04:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,-- we don't need our eyes to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.80,0:04:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,understand it's not safe to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.98,0:04:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.17,0:04:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or we listen for quick
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.99,0:04:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,confirmations every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When you put on your seatbelt
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.82,0:04:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[seatbelt click], you don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.72,0:04:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to double check it's fastened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.36,0:04:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear the click, and you know
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.61,0:04:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We can also listen for more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.83,0:04:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,nuanced things, like the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.61,0:04:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of someone's footsteps may tell
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.53,0:04:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,us something about their
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.42,0:04:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,emotional state
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[slow footsteps].
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.71,0:04:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.50,0:05:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they in a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.91,0:05:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we know a person very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.69,0:05:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we may even recognize them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by the sound of their footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[footstep sounds].
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.49,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we hear has a big impact
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.47,0:05:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,on how we feel and what we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and sound helps us make sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the things going on around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.04,0:05:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we know that sound is such a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.61,0:05:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful medium.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.54,0:05:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we use it in our design?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.50,0:05:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people think that design is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.45,0:05:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about what a product looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.91,0:05:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or at Apple we pay a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,attention to, how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We think design is also about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.14,0:05:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what it feels like and what it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.73,0:05:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.78,0:05:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the role of sound in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.73,0:05:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,design?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.94,0:05:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like using a universal
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,language that is already
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.52,0:05:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,understood by everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.10,0:05:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps shape the experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.70,0:06:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a product.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps us understand
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.60,0:06:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.61,0:06:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gives our devices a voice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can tell us things, they
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.87,0:06:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,can talk back to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.38,0:06:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So if your iPhone is playing a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.17,0:06:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sound, what is it trying to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[beeping].
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.61,0:06:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You just used Apple Pay
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.84,0:06:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.55,0:06:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[beeping].
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.83,0:06:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe it didn't go so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.55,0:06:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Try again, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.14,0:06:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[beeping].
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody just texted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Alarm ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.05,0:06:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Or good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.31,0:06:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.52,0:06:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Alarm ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.05,0:06:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Or at the end of the day [music]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost time to go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Many times though, when an app
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,plays a sound, we don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.86,0:06:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.27,0:06:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.77,0:06:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[beeping].
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.05,0:06:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to look at our screen to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:06:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,understand what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.05,0:07:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a way for our phone to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.73,0:07:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Hey, look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.32,0:07:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Something happened, but I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.56,0:07:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,really know what."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a very intelligent way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of communicating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.18,0:07:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we improve on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.78,0:07:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if your app relies on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications, it makes a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.94,0:07:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sense to think about creating
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.09,0:07:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,your own notification sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.01,0:07:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want people to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.85,0:07:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,experience when they receive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.70,0:07:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that notification?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want people to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's coming from your app?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.14,0:07:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't do this, you are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.65,0:07:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,stuck with the default we just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.96,0:07:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,heard, and it doesn't really say
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,much about where it's coming
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from and what it means, so it's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.50,0:07:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a missed opportunity to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.99,0:07:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,distinguish your app, your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.07,0:07:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,unique identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.67,0:07:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, before, when we were in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,forest, we heard the Dark Sky
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.54,0:07:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,notification, and Dark Sky is a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.03,0:07:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,weather app, and it sends this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.23,0:07:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,notification when rain is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.94,0:07:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It does this pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.99,0:07:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's listen to it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.10,0:08:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And why does this work so well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[beeping].
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This sound is easily
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.67,0:08:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hear this, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's coming from Dark Sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.11,0:08:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It conveys a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.81,0:08:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a direct recording of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.57,0:08:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,raindrops, but it has this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.06,0:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,liquid quality to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.37,0:08:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps you connect the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to the message it's sending.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.78,0:08:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a friendly sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.74,0:08:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not jarring, but telling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you in a friendly way it's time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to find cover soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.10,0:08:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a simple and clean
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.03,0:08:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,sound, quite pleasant to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.75,0:08:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.29,0:08:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's try this ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's create a sound for an app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.69,0:08:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we? Well, first we need an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,app, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, luckily, some years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.94,0:08:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,our prototyping team did a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.11,0:08:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called "Fake It Till You
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.54,0:08:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Make It."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.91,0:08:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about creating fake apps
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to learn from how
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.09,0:08:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,people would interact with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.33,0:08:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They create an app called Toast
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.55,0:08:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Modern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.42,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, maybe some of you know that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,toast has become very popular in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,San Francisco, and people pay a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.92,0:09:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of money for a slice of what
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.15,0:09:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,some call hipster toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.79,0:09:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Toast Modern, the app they
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,created, helps you find
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,overpriced artisanal toast on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.13,0:09:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the streets of San Francisco
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.36,0:09:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter] and share this with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.42,0:09:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your friends and family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.95,0:09:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if someone sends you some
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.18,0:09:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,newly discovered toast, you get
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.63,0:09:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.82,0:09:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can create a sound for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.20,0:09:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.74,0:09:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We can start by asking ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,some questions, like, "What is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of what this app is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.40,0:09:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,about?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.82,0:09:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in this case, simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.55,0:09:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about finding toast and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.25,0:09:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,sharing it with your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What emotion do we want to evoke
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.64,0:09:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,here when people receive this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,notification?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.73,0:09:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we want them to be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:09:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they found some new toast to try
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.97,0:10:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and eager to try it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.85,0:10:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we match the app's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetics?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.99,0:10:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We just saw the screen, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.63,0:10:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,looks pretty functional and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.02,0:10:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,simple, so let's keep the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.78,0:10:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,similar to that, keep it simple
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.62,0:10:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we notice, we can start
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with some sound sources.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We can record some sounds to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.52,0:10:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,inspired by.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.33,0:10:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, let's just get
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.39,0:10:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get a toaster and record
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.22,0:10:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,those sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.51,0:10:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's exactly what we did,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and here are some of the sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.98,0:10:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.49,0:10:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Toaster popping ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.96,0:10:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Toaster ejecting toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Spreading butter on a piece of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.53,0:10:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bread Crumbling ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.54,0:10:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of toast breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.06,0:10:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And taking a bite out of a piece
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.66,0:10:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.67,0:10:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can also create a little
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.08,0:10:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,bit of a story from the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.03,0:10:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning to the end, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.08,0:10:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,making toast and eating toast,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and record the whole process.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.02,0:11:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[toaster popping].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.02,0:11:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[timer ticking].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[chiming].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.02,0:11:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[scraping toast].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[toast crunching].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.44,0:11:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.86,0:11:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now we have a nice
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.71,0:11:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,palette.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice we added some sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.23,0:11:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to this, because in the initial
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,set, there was not that timer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.92,0:11:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sound and the chime sounds, so
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.24,0:11:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we recorded those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we can start making
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.10,0:11:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,notification sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.29,0:11:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one sound that I like
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.37,0:11:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.60,0:11:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[toast crunching].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very characteristic, but
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe it doesn't work so well as
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.47,0:11:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,a notification coming from your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.65,0:11:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,phone every day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.68,0:11:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.72,0:11:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So how about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.45,0:11:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[timer ticking].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[chiming].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this little timer sound
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.68,0:11:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the chime, but the only
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.71,0:11:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,thing I don't really like about
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.85,0:11:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the sound of the toaster
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.76,0:11:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ejecting the toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.72,0:11:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:11:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can find a more expensive
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.70,0:12:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,toaster maybe, that'll sound
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.27,0:12:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,better, or we can construct our
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,own toaster sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.47,0:12:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But why don't we just take away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.85,0:12:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the parts we don't like and see
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.81,0:12:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're left with?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.51,0:12:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take that sound out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.98,0:12:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[timer ticking].
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[chiming].
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.11,0:12:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, this might work pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what it looks like
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.27,0:12:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when the notification comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.02,0:12:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[timer ticking].
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.52,0:12:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,[chiming].
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.27,0:12:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is pretty good for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.58,0:12:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now remember, we're just trying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.27,0:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just prototyping.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.94,0:12:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the app is fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.11,0:12:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, we're not all
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.79,0:12:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,sound designers, but once we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,start working with a sound
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.08,0:12:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,designer, they can take this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,inspiration and maybe create
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.85,0:12:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,something that's more unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,more ownable, and maybe more
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.75,0:12:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract, like the Dark Sky
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.23,0:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.48,0:12:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what did the creative
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.96,0:12:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,process look like here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We started out with all these
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,toast recordings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the blue dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.98,0:12:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we realized we needed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.34,0:13:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,some other sounds to complete
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.71,0:13:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the palette, so we added the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.28,0:13:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,timer sound and the chime sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.82,0:13:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the yellow ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.29,0:13:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we created some
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.25,0:13:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,candidates and tried them out on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.01,0:13:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,our device.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.63,0:13:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We found out that a lot of these
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds didn't really work so
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.57,0:13:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,well, so we ended up with the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,timer and the chime sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.32,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now why am I showing you this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.66,0:13:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it illustrates how often
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.21,0:13:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we start out with this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.08,0:13:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,assumption that something might
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.49,0:13:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,work, but then we find out that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.84,0:13:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,going this exploration phase, we
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.88,0:13:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,find out that what we really
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.59,0:13:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,need is something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.15,0:13:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go through this to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.81,0:13:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,understand that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,First we have to make mistakes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to come up with something great.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.53,0:13:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what kind of sound sources
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.36,0:13:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,can you record when you do an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.49,0:13:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,exploration like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.23,0:13:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You could record an acoustic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.67,0:13:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,instrument or an electronic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.22,0:13:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,instrument, like a synthesizer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.82,0:13:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,software or hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.41,0:13:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, we found out you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.74,0:14:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,record anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.96,0:14:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that makes a sound can
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.70,0:14:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,be an inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.93,0:14:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now at Apple, we use any of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.73,0:14:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,these sound sources.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.40,0:14:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It really depends on the project
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.67,0:14:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we're working on, and some of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.36,0:14:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,them are easily recognizable
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.49,0:14:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These sounds may be played
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of times per day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier this year, Tim mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that at one point during the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.82,0:14:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Super Bowl, 380,000 messages
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.07,0:14:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,were sent per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.96,0:14:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Never though in the history of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.60,0:14:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound has it been played
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.27,0:14:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,live on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.01,0:14:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, nobody ever thought of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.34,0:14:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.47,0:14:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But today's a special today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.79,0:14:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So ladies and gentlemen, for the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.56,0:15:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,first time in the history of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.49,0:15:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,this sound since it was
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced with iOS 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.55,0:15:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentration.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I hit the right one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[bell ringing].
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.52,0:15:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.67,0:15:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.99,0:15:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We use this notification sound
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,for messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.26,0:15:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does this work well for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,messages?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.22,0:15:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to think about, when
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.33,0:15:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,will people hear this sound, and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.20,0:15:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what will they be doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.74,0:15:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They have their phones in a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.03,0:15:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,pocket, in their jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.07,0:15:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they are on a busy city
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.23,0:15:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,street or an airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.43,0:16:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to cut through the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.71,0:16:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,noise of these locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs to be very clean and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.29,0:16:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,simple, but there's another
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.48,0:16:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that is important that we
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.89,0:16:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,don't really want to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.73,0:16:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,convey the information of what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.56,0:16:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you're sending.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.99,0:16:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very different than the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.41,0:16:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dark Sky notification that can
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.68,0:16:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,only mean one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.66,0:16:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, it can mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.99,0:16:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,anything, anything you're
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,sending with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.79,0:16:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want it to be very neutral
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.24,0:16:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.76,0:16:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this here is a kalimba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.19,0:16:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you've seen one before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.46,0:16:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what it sounds like.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.52,0:16:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Kalimba playing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You recognize it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[kalimba playing].
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.52,0:16:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughter ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.41,0:16:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So we recorded this sound as the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.87,0:17:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,default notification for --
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.84,0:17:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.48,0:17:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Calendar, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.02,0:17:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.10,0:17:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bit more of a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.24,0:17:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristic sound, because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a very common
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.77,0:17:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,instrument, but again, it's very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.01,0:17:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,simple and clear as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.63,0:17:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when we were designing for
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the watch, we asked our self the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,question, how can we be inspired
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.17,0:17:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by this beautiful industrial
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.72,0:17:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,design of this device?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.87,0:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can we create the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.68,0:17:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion that what you hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.42,0:17:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that the sounds are actually
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,made by the device itself, that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.81,0:17:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they're coming from the device
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.20,0:17:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So we decided to record the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,different materials, the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.23,0:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,stainless steel, the aluminum,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.60,0:17:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.22,0:17:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I have here is the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.87,0:17:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,housing of a stainless steel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.81,0:17:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.95,0:17:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can hit that in different
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.66,0:17:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ways and see if it makes a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.46,0:17:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:17:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ringing sound].
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.42,0:18:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hang it up, try a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.32,0:18:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.55,0:18:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ringing sound].
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.91,0:18:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit it the right way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.18,0:18:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,[ringing sound].
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually sounds quite nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.10,0:18:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So we decided to use this as an
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.18,0:18:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,inspiration, and we used these
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.84,0:18:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,actual recordings for some of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the sounds that are on your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.57,0:18:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,watch today, like [ringing] the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.88,0:18:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,notification and the watch ring
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.52,0:18:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Ringing sound ]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So together with haptics, what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.48,0:18:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel, what you see, and what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.35,0:18:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear really come together
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,here in one experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.66,0:18:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you may still think, "I have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.06,0:18:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,no idea how to record a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.65,0:18:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never done that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.28,0:18:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well we've got some very simple
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.63,0:18:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tools you can start with,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.10,0:18:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,already on your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.02,0:18:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's Voice Memos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.04,0:18:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great recording app.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.59,0:18:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You can record any kind of sound
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.14,0:18:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:18:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's Music Memos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.04,0:18:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can download it for free
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.65,0:19:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,from the app store, and it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.97,0:19:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,great tool for more musical
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.97,0:19:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ideas, and it works really well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.88,0:19:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with Garage Band.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.20,0:19:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, Garage Band
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.06,0:19:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,can be used on your Mac to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.33,0:19:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,record sounds and edit sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And for those who want to dive a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.25,0:19:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,little deeper, there's always
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.45,0:19:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic Pro, a great tool for the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.19,0:19:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,more seasoned users.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.77,0:19:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So to recap, what are the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.18,0:19:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics of a good
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.25,0:19:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,notification sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's distinguishable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.26,0:19:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You know which app is sending
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.05,0:19:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.74,0:19:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It matches the design of the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.20,0:19:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.46,0:19:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're creating an app that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,looks very cartoony, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.17,0:19:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You may want to look at some
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.77,0:19:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds that really match that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.73,0:19:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,aesthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.76,0:19:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if your app is very
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.25,0:19:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,minimalist, then maybe you want
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.05,0:19:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to start with some very simple
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.07,0:19:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.01,0:19:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unobtrusive and repeatable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.32,0:19:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that even if you use
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.72,0:19:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it multiple times per day that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.73,0:19:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't become annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.14,0:19:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A great way to try this out is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.56,0:20:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,just to put it on your phone for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.22,0:20:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a little while, for a week or
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.22,0:20:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so, and live with it for a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.89,0:20:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.06,0:20:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If after a week you still like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound, it's probably a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.16,0:20:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.06,0:20:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.71,0:20:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It cuts through noise, but it's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.37,0:20:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not abrasive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.48,0:20:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.14,0:20:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, let's look at designing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.75,0:20:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,sound for UI elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now every object you interact
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.35,0:20:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with in the real world makes a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.64,0:20:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,sound, so it's very natural to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.83,0:20:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,expect that an object you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,makes a sound as well, but we
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.15,0:20:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,definitely don't do this for
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.82,0:20:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,every interaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.32,0:20:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We really try to find the right
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.51,0:20:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,balance between no sound and too
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.72,0:20:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.30,0:20:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So UI sounds are things like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.62,0:21:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard sounds, scrolling
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.31,0:21:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds, pressing a button,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.26,0:21:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,tapping, swiping, or any kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.08,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,transitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.65,0:21:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I want to focus on three of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.83,0:21:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,these and see how we approach
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.51,0:21:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,them in our own devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.31,0:21:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.30,0:21:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.42,0:21:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now following our previous
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.84,0:21:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,design strategy, we may want to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,start by recording some actual
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.41,0:21:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboards, like an old
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.87,0:21:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,typewriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.52,0:21:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Typewriter clicking ]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.07,0:21:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this rattles quite a bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.61,0:21:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's something satisfying
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.34,0:21:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about the letters hitting the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.63,0:21:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.09,0:21:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.60,0:21:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How about a computer keyboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Typing sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.06,0:21:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something pleasant about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.28,0:21:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this sound as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.49,0:21:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not very static.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.97,0:21:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.48,0:21:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So not every key sounds the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.75,0:21:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,same.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.06,0:22:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can remember this when we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.42,0:22:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,create our own sound for our iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.82,0:22:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.48,0:22:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We're designing for software, so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.01,0:22:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we can make it sound any way we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.81,0:22:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,want.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.87,0:22:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, we can change the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.70,0:22:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sound of the space bar, of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.31,0:22:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,modifier keys, and the backspace
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.01,0:22:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.50,0:22:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's listen to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.02,0:22:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Popping sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.07,0:22:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we create a character that is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.54,0:22:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a bit more playful and not so
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.09,0:22:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,static.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.60,0:22:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do another thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.19,0:22:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When you type faster, we bring
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.23,0:22:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,down the volume of the sound
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.69,0:22:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,ever so slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.09,0:22:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not something that you may
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.18,0:22:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,hear in everyday use, but even
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,these little things make a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.07,0:22:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.01,0:22:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's listen to it one more
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.46,0:22:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.52,0:23:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Popping sounds ]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.09,0:23:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now next it's pressing a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.66,0:23:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.50,0:23:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,For those of you with an iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.91,0:23:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,7, I invite you to bring it up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.64,0:23:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to your ear and click the Home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.38,0:23:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,button a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.05,0:23:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.41,0:23:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it sound like?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.35,0:23:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now since the iPhone 7, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.26,0:23:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a solid, safe Home button.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.40,0:23:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's durable, and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.51,0:23:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,waterproof, but it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.77,0:23:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,actually move or make a "click"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.29,0:23:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.43,0:23:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we used the Taptic Engine to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.30,0:23:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,create this button experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.42,0:23:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and we learned while designing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.82,0:23:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for the watch that combining
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds and haptics the right way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.20,0:23:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and synchronizing them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.72,0:23:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,precisely, we can come up with
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.42,0:23:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,this great multisensory
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.75,0:23:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, and we were looking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.28,0:23:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for a similar experience for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.39,0:23:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this button, so we decided to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.42,0:24:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,add a very subtle, quiet "click"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,sound to the tap of the Taptic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.76,0:24:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Engine, resulting in what you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.60,0:24:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,hear right now when you press
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.66,0:24:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.27,0:24:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And this also allowed us to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.61,0:24:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,create multiple "click" fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.65,0:24:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you set up a new iPhone,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.44,0:24:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you can choose between two
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.46,0:24:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,different clicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.72,0:24:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one more thing that was
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,very interesting when we were
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.69,0:24:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,doing this exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.62,0:24:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We found out that, if you take
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.39,0:24:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one haptic tap, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.40,0:24:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,synthesize it to a very sharp
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.85,0:24:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and precise sound, like the one
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.70,0:24:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on the left here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.50,0:24:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.72,0:24:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Clicking sound ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.05,0:24:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And people think that what they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.69,0:24:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,feel is very precise and sharp
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.96,0:24:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as well, but if we take exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.57,0:24:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the same tap, exactly the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.20,0:24:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't change anything, and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.06,0:24:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,synchronize it to another sound
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.53,0:24:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,like this [sound], then people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.08,0:24:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,think that what they feel is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.49,0:24:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,very different.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.51,0:24:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's less sharp and less
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.59,0:24:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.27,0:24:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really interesting how
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.59,0:24:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we can fool ourselves using
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.53,0:25:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,sound this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.36,0:25:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, let's look at
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.90,0:25:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,transitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.21,0:25:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the sounds that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.29,0:25:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,accompany a movement between two
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.41,0:25:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,different states, like in the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.82,0:25:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.97,0:25:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking for two things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.46,0:25:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.02,0:25:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A feeling of depth and a feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.71,0:25:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.45,0:25:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's listen to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.18,0:25:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Transition sound ]
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.71,0:25:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So the special character of this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.47,0:25:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,sound emphasizes the feeling of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.14,0:25:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,depth, and the envelope of the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.04,0:25:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sound is shaped in a way similar
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.80,0:25:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to that of an object passing you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.04,0:25:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by, creating that feeling of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.63,0:25:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.68,0:25:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We could have used another sound
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.20,0:25:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with similar characteristics,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.52,0:25:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but you really also want it to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.45,0:25:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,match the aesthetic of the Apple
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.94,0:25:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,TV user interface perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.73,0:25:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We think this sound does the job
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.69,0:25:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.63,0:25:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's also a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.60,0:25:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,direction, because we have two
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.73,0:25:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,different sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.43,0:25:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know if you're moving
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.38,0:25:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,forward or backward.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.10,0:26:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's listen to it one more
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.86,0:26:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.52,0:26:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Forward transition sound ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.83,0:26:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Backward transition sound ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.99,0:26:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are the characteristics
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.20,0:26:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of good UI sound design?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.06,0:26:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,First off, it's used sparingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.71,0:26:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, again, try to find a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.12,0:26:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,balance between no sound and too
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.07,0:26:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.01,0:26:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a delicate balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.57,0:26:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a much lower volume than
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.96,0:26:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a notification sound, because
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.08,0:26:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,people have their phones in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.19,0:26:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.03,0:26:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We can keep it very quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.30,0:26:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We only want to add a very
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.42,0:26:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,subtle layer to the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.88,0:26:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they help the users, and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.70,0:26:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they delight the user by
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.13,0:26:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,creating this great visceral
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.04,0:26:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,experience combined with haptics
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.19,0:26:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.12,0:26:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in this last section, I'd
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.46,0:26:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,like to give you some tips and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.91,0:26:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,techniques to keep in mind when
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.04,0:26:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you're working on your own app.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.74,0:27:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, keep sound in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.96,0:27:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.52,0:27:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're beginning your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.50,0:27:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,project, you can ask yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.24,0:27:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.85,0:27:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Will my app send frequent
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.03,0:27:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.09,0:27:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If this is the case, it makes a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.92,0:27:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of sense to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.17,0:27:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,creating your own notification
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.41,0:27:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.46,0:27:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Can sound play a role in my
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.51,0:27:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,app's branding?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.16,0:27:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if the answer to the first
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.49,0:27:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,question is yes, and you do
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.37,0:27:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,create your own sound, then it's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.06,0:27:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,already playing a role.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.87,0:27:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're already creating a voice
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.03,0:27:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for your brand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.05,0:27:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now how can the UI benefit from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.60,0:27:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,an audible component?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.96,0:27:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any way you can help
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.80,0:27:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,people understand what's going
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.93,0:27:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on on the screen by adding some
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.63,0:27:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,subtle sounds to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.66,0:27:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then how would I understand
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.30,0:27:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,my app without a graphical user
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.77,0:27:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,interface?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.08,0:27:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The question I started out with.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.27,0:27:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you don't have to use
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.71,0:27:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,your app without looking at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.33,0:27:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's an interesting question
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.21,0:27:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to help yourself, and it may
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.22,0:27:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,help you come up with some
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.83,0:28:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,innovative ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.33,0:28:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an important one.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.90,0:28:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence is golden.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.45,0:28:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It may sound funny from a sound
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.11,0:28:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,designer, but the absence of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.26,0:28:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,sound is as important as adding
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.99,0:28:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.87,0:28:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Really try to find the right
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.46,0:28:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.32,0:28:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If we wouldn't do this, our Maps
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.55,0:28:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,app could easily sound like
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.38,0:28:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.52,0:28:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Different sounds playing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.02,0:28:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughter ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.52,0:28:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Different sounds playing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.48,0:28:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 3D.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.74,0:28:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Laughter ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.31,0:28:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Different sounds playing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.61,0:28:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,>> A bit much, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.89,0:28:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[applause].
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.54,0:28:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.54,0:28:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,creating a game, it makes a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.18,0:29:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of sense to come up with a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.63,0:29:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,world of sound, like a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.94,0:29:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,sound world that fits your game
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.73,0:29:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.76,0:29:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't want every app to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.07,0:29:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sound like a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.10,0:29:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you do add UI sounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.23,0:29:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,also add the option for people
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.64,0:29:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.72,0:29:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the last thing we want is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.63,0:29:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for people to always hit the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.58,0:29:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,ringer switch, or even worst,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.40,0:29:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,delete your app because they
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.59,0:29:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,don't like the way it sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.74,0:29:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So be very careful when adding
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.59,0:29:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,these sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.22,0:29:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do, add the option
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.76,0:29:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for people to turn them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.54,0:29:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as much as you pay
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.59,0:29:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,attention to every single detail
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.93,0:29:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the visual design of your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.24,0:29:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,app, do the same thing for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.17,0:29:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.11,0:29:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's some things to keep in
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.04,0:29:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,mind, especially when designing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.80,0:29:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for a device like the iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.28,0:29:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm listening to music, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.27,0:29:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,your notification sound comes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.52,0:29:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in, the music ducks, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.45,0:29:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,fine because I choose to get
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.89,0:29:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,these notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.92,0:29:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They give me information.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.28,0:29:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But if your notification sound
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.81,0:30:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is too long, it ducks for a very
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.04,0:30:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,long time, so it becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.82,0:30:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.60,0:30:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So ask yourself the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.32,0:30:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,does it get in the way of the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.36,0:30:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,user in any way?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.10,0:30:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We all know how frustrating it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.27,0:30:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is if you're watching a video,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.87,0:30:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you hear doesn't line
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.07,0:30:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up with what you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.52,0:30:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[footstep sounds].
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.20,0:30:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it gives us this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.92,0:30:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,uneasy feeling that something is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.52,0:30:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,not right here, and it's so much
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.77,0:30:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,more satisfying when everything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.78,0:30:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,lines up nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.85,0:30:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[footsteps sounds].
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.06,0:30:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're adding sound to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.18,0:30:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,haptics or animation, then
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.98,0:30:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,really try to find the right
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.29,0:30:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,moment to synchronize to.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.71,0:30:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that adding sounds to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.14,0:30:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,haptics, that pushing it back or
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.05,0:30:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,forward by as little as ten
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.96,0:30:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,milliseconds sometimes makes a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.86,0:30:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in the experience, so
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.01,0:30:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,really experiment with this a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.66,0:31:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit and try to find the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.07,0:31:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,right timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.54,0:31:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now for a couple more pro tips,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.32,0:31:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a spectrogram.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.55,0:31:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a visual representation of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.08,0:31:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a sound and of the frequency
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.61,0:31:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,present in a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.50,0:31:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The brighter the color, the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.64,0:31:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,louder that frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.26,0:31:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular sound sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.71,0:31:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.52,0:31:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bell ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.65,0:31:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something that can be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.62,0:31:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,improved upon here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.15,0:31:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,First off, there's a bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.69,0:31:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,silence in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.14,0:31:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The actual sound starts here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.77,0:31:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I don't know if you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.91,0:31:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,heard it, but there was a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.37,0:31:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,noise in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.71,0:31:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see it on the screen as
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.86,0:31:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.03,0:31:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the visual noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.89,0:31:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the sound was truncated
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.31,0:31:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end, so it cuts off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.68,0:31:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds very unnatural.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.14,0:31:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now a professional with some
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.47,0:31:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,expensive software can easily
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.75,0:31:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,make it sound like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.52,0:31:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bell ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.07,0:31:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's much cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.01,0:32:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The background is darker, less
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.49,0:32:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,noise there, and it fades out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.68,0:32:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.93,0:32:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But like I said, you need some
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.36,0:32:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,expensive software for it, or do
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.93,0:32:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you really?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.53,0:32:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we found that using
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.49,0:32:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Garage Band, you can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.11,0:32:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,come pretty close.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.34,0:32:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can adjust the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the region, stripping out the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.62,0:32:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,silence, and then you can fade
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.44,0:32:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out the sound using track
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.60,0:32:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,automation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.13,0:32:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We found a preset called iChat
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.42,0:32:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Voice that has a denoiser
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.80,0:32:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,function.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.09,0:32:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's meant to be used for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.15,0:32:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,speech, but you can use it for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.24,0:32:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,any kind of sound, and we can
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.61,0:32:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,come up with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.68,0:32:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Bell ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.09,0:32:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's much cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.63,0:32:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're inventive, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.32,0:32:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,come a long way with a simple
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.57,0:32:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,tool like Garage Band as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.73,0:32:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Also pay attention to the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.93,0:32:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,frequencies you're playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.37,0:32:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The iPhone speaker is a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.87,0:32:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful speaker, but there are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.90,0:32:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,some physical limitations,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.62,0:32:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,especially low frequencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.23,0:32:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It may not translate that well,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.08,0:32:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so it makes sense to filter out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.75,0:32:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,those frequencies that you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.05,0:32:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,use.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.10,0:33:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This will clean up the sound and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.30,0:33:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,makes it sound more clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.64,0:33:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you find out what works
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.49,0:33:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and what doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.87,0:33:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just test it out on the device
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.60,0:33:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's going to be played
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.46,0:33:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.74,0:33:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're creating a game
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.60,0:33:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that will run on iPhone as well
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.68,0:33:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,as on iPad, then test out the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.49,0:33:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds on the iPhone as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.75,0:33:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,on the iPad, and realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.09,0:33:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,people will be wearing
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.91,0:33:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,headphones, so also test it out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.21,0:33:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for headphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.74,0:33:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when you're done exploring
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.25,0:33:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and done prototyping, maybe it's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.74,0:33:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,time to work with an expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.55,0:33:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to get serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.57,0:33:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So a sound designer can help you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.02,0:33:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,come with an overall sound
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.21,0:33:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,concept and help you design the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.35,0:33:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds, and a sound engineer can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.86,0:33:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,help you clean these sounds up
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.47,0:33:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and make them ready for everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.48,0:33:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,use.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.55,0:33:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we all know this guy, and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.95,0:33:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,even I have to admit I use it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.97,0:33:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.06,0:34:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal is not for everyone to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.44,0:34:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,leave their sound on all the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.92,0:34:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,time, everywhere they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.38,0:34:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we start hearing more
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.02,0:34:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and more wonderful notifications
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.32,0:34:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and UI sounds that help our
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.42,0:34:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,users and delight our users,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.64,0:34:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then maybe, just maybe, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.21,0:34:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,start seeing people reach for it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.93,0:34:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a little less.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.40,0:34:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That will be awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.86,0:34:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for listening to me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.78,0:34:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,today.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.52,0:34:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
